01:00:34.264 --> 01:00:36.971
[male reporter]by 1988 though,
cassette sales nearly doubled,

01:00:37.267 --> 01:00:39.804
cds had exploded,
and the market for vinyl lps

01:00:40.103 --> 01:00:42.594
had shrunk
by nearly two thirds.

01:00:42.897 --> 01:00:44.808
so it was exciting
for the record company,

01:00:45.108 --> 01:00:45.972
it was exciting
for the consumer,

01:00:46.276 --> 01:00:48.312
and for the artist.

01:00:48.611 --> 01:00:51.318
all of a sudden, you sold
you were rich.

01:00:51.614 --> 01:00:53.821
[steve knopper]all of this
flowed from the fact that

01:00:54.117 --> 01:00:56.859
the cd was selling so well.

01:00:57.162 --> 01:00:58.868
and Tower, of course
benefited from that,

01:00:59.164 --> 01:01:00.779
they were part
of that culture too.

01:01:01.082 --> 01:01:02.788
[male reporter]in response
to this consumer defection,

01:01:03.084 --> 01:01:05.120
a number of major record stores
have removed vinyl albums

01:01:05.420 --> 01:01:07.126
from their shelves altogether.

01:01:07.422 --> 01:01:09.538
so, is vinyl dead?

01:01:09.841 --> 01:01:11.206
[female reporter]
today's popular music

01:01:11.509 --> 01:01:12.965
is more diverse
than ever before,

01:01:13.261 --> 01:01:15.593
and selection is
at an all-time high.

01:01:15.889 --> 01:01:17.174
but the cost
of pre-recorded music

01:01:17.474 --> 01:01:18.759
has also reached new levels,

01:01:19.058 --> 01:01:20.548
causing customers to be wary

01:01:20.852 --> 01:01:23.093
of purchasing unknown artists
and musical styles.

01:01:23.396 --> 01:01:26.308
Tower and the record labels
were doing this dance on price

01:01:26.608 --> 01:01:29.850
that suppliers
and wholesalers often do

01:01:30.153 --> 01:01:33.111
which is sort of:
"where will the consumer break?"

01:01:33.406 --> 01:01:34.862
to combat this problem,

01:01:35.158 --> 01:01:37.365
Tower has introduced
their new cd listening stations

01:01:37.660 --> 01:01:39.571
in its retail
locations worldwide,

01:01:39.871 --> 01:01:42.658
and the public's reaction
has been tremendous.

01:01:42.957 --> 01:01:45.699
but I think where russ said
and where Tower Records said,
they were just like,

01:01:46.002 --> 01:01:48.789
" every christmas
the records cost more,
and they're selling more."

01:01:49.088 --> 01:01:50.828
what's not to like?

01:01:51.132 --> 01:01:53.088
[russ on tv]
our stores are bigger,
they're better stocked,

01:01:53.384 --> 01:01:54.590
they have
more knowledgeable people.

01:01:54.886 --> 01:01:56.547
competition will
take care of itself.

